title: Do vaccination rates differ by country?
analysis_commentary: In 2011/12, all four UK countries had a high percentage of children (by their first birthday) completing a primary course of the combined diphtheria, tetanus, polio, pertussis and haemophilus influenzae b immunisation, and the two standalone meningococcal group C and pneumococcal disease immunisations (>94%). There was also a high percentage of children having their first dose of the MMR immunisation by their second birthday (>90%). England consistently had the lowest coverage when compared to the other countries.
data_source: NHS England & Public Health England & Health & Social Care Information Centre
